items.name: Account
docs: The full account information for a particular account ID.

items.name: ExtrinsicCount
docs: Total extrinsics count for the current block.

items.name: BlockWeight
docs: The current weight for the block.

items.name: AllExtrinsicsLen
docs: Total length (in bytes) for all extrinsics put together, for the current block.

items.name: BlockHash
docs: Map of block numbers to block hashes.

items.name: ExtrinsicData
docs: Extrinsics data for the current block (maps an extrinsic's index to its data).

items.name: Number
docs: The current block number being processed. Set by `execute_block`.

items.name: ParentHash
docs: Hash of the previous block.

items.name: Digest
docs: Digest of the current block, also part of the block header.

items.name: Events
docs: Events deposited for the current block.

items.name: EventCount
docs: The number of events in the `Events<T>` list.

items.name: EventTopics
docs: Mapping between a topic (represented by T::Hash) and a vector of indexes
of events in the `<Events<T>>` list.
All topic vectors have deterministic storage locations depending on the topic. This
allows light-clients to leverage the changes trie storage tracking mechanism and
in case of changes fetch the list of events of interest.
The value has the type `(T::BlockNumber, EventIndex)` because if we used only just
the `EventIndex` then in case if the topic has the same contents on the next block
no notification will be triggered thus the event might be lost.

items.name: LastRuntimeUpgrade
docs: Stores the `spec_version` and `spec_name` of when the last runtime upgrade happened.

items.name: UpgradedToU32RefCount
docs: True if we have upgraded so that `type RefCount` is `u32`. False (default) if not.

items.name: UpgradedToTripleRefCount
docs: True if we have upgraded so that AccountInfo contains three types of `RefCount`. False
(default) if not.

items.name: ExecutionPhase
docs: The execution phase of the block.

constants.name: BlockWeights
docs: Block & extrinsics weights: base values and limits.

constants.name: BlockLength
docs: The maximum length of a block (in bytes).

constants.name: BlockHashCount
docs: Maximum number of block number to block hash mappings to keep (oldest pruned first).

constants.name: DbWeight
docs: The weight of runtime database operations the runtime can invoke.

constants.name: Version
docs: Get the chain's current version.

constants.name: SS58Prefix
docs: The designated SS85 prefix of this chain.
This replaces the "ss58Format" property declared in the chain spec. Reason is
that the runtime should know about the prefix in order to make use of it as
an identifier of the chain.

items.name: EpochIndex
docs: Current epoch index.

items.name: Authorities
docs: Current epoch authorities.

items.name: GenesisSlot
docs: The slot at which the first epoch actually started. This is 0
until the first block of the chain.

items.name: CurrentSlot
docs: Current slot number.

items.name: Randomness
docs: The epoch randomness for the *current* epoch.
# Security
This MUST NOT be used for gambling, as it can be influenced by a
malicious validator in the short term. It MAY be used in many
cryptographic protocols, however, so long as one remembers that this
(like everything else on-chain) it is public. For example, it can be
used where a number is needed that cannot have been chosen by an
adversary, for purposes such as public-coin zero-knowledge proofs.

items.name: PendingEpochConfigChange
docs: Pending epoch configuration change that will be applied when the next epoch is enacted.

items.name: NextRandomness
docs: Next epoch randomness.

items.name: NextAuthorities
docs: Next epoch authorities.

items.name: SegmentIndex
docs: Randomness under construction.
We make a tradeoff between storage accesses and list length.
We store the under-construction randomness in segments of up to
`UNDER_CONSTRUCTION_SEGMENT_LENGTH`.
Once a segment reaches this length, we begin the next one.
We reset all segments and return to `0` at the beginning of every
epoch.

items.name: UnderConstruction
docs: TWOX-NOTE: `SegmentIndex` is an increasing integer, so this is okay.

items.name: Initialized
docs: Temporary value (cleared at block finalization) which is `Some`
if per-block initialization has already been called for current block.

items.name: AuthorVrfRandomness
docs: This field should always be populated during block processing unless
secondary plain slots are enabled (which don't contain a VRF output).
It is set in `on_initialize`, before it will contain the value from the last block.

items.name: EpochStart
docs: The block numbers when the last and current epoch have started, respectively `N-1` and
NOTE: We track this is in order to annotate the block number when a given pool of
entropy was fixed (i.e. it was known to chain observers). Since epochs are defined in
slots, which may be skipped, the block numbers may not line up with the slot numbers.

items.name: Lateness
docs: How late the current block is compared to its parent.
This entry is populated as part of block execution and is cleaned up
on block finalization. Querying this storage entry outside of block
execution context should always yield zero.

items.name: EpochConfig
docs: The configuration for the current epoch. Should never be `None` as it is initialized in genesis.

items.name: NextEpochConfig
docs: The configuration for the next epoch, `None` if the config will not change
(you can fallback to `EpochConfig` instead in that case).

constants.name: EpochDuration
docs: The amount of time, in slots, that each epoch should last.
NOTE: Currently it is not possible to change the epoch duration after
the chain has started. Attempting to do so will brick block production.

constants.name: ExpectedBlockTime
docs: The expected average block time at which BABE should be creating
blocks. Since BABE is probabilistic it is not trivial to figure out
what the expected average block time should be based on the slot
duration and the security parameter `c` (where `1 - c` represents
the probability of a slot being empty).

items.name: Now
docs: Current time for the current block.

items.name: DidUpdate
docs: Did the timestamp get updated in this block?

constants.name: MinimumPeriod
docs: The minimum period between blocks. Beware that this is different to the *expected* period
that the block production apparatus provides. Your chosen consensus system will generally
work with this to determine a sensible block time. e.g. For Aura, it will be double this
period on default settings.

items.name: Uncles
docs: Uncles

items.name: Author
docs: Author of current block.

items.name: DidSetUncles
docs: Whether uncles were already set in this block.

constants.name: UncleGenerations
docs: The number of blocks back we should accept uncles.
This means that we will deal with uncle-parents that are
`UncleGenerations + 1` before `now`.

items.name: Accounts
docs: The lookup from index to account.

constants.name: Deposit
docs: The deposit needed for reserving an index.

items.name: TotalIssuance
docs: The total units issued in the system.

items.name: Account
docs: The balance of an account.
NOTE: This is only used in the case that this pallet is used to store balances.

items.name: Locks
docs: Any liquidity locks on some account balances.
NOTE: Should only be accessed when setting, changing and freeing a lock.

items.name: Reserves
docs: Named reserves on some account balances.

items.name: StorageVersion
docs: Storage version of the pallet.
This is set to v2.0.0 for new networks.

constants.name: ExistentialDeposit
docs: The minimum amount required to keep an account open.

constants.name: MaxLocks
docs: The maximum number of locks that should exist on an account.
Not strictly enforced, but used for weight estimation.

constants.name: MaxReserves
docs: The maximum number of named reserves that can exist on an account.

constants.name: TransactionByteFee
docs: The fee to be paid for making a transaction; the per-byte portion.

constants.name: WeightToFee
docs: The polynomial that is applied in order to derive fee from weight.

items.name: Round
docs: Internal counter for the number of rounds.
This is useful for de-duplication of transactions submitted to the pool, and general
diagnostics of the pallet.
This is merely incremented once per every time that an upstream `elect` is called.

items.name: CurrentPhase
docs: Current phase.

items.name: QueuedSolution
docs: Current best solution, signed or unsigned, queued to be returned upon `elect`.

items.name: Snapshot
docs: Snapshot data of the round.
This is created at the beginning of the signed phase and cleared upon calling `elect`.

items.name: DesiredTargets
docs: Desired number of targets to elect for this round.
Only exists when [`Snapshot`] is present.

items.name: SnapshotMetadata
docs: The metadata of the [`RoundSnapshot`]
Only exists when [`Snapshot`] is present.

items.name: SignedSubmissionNextIndex
docs: The next index to be assigned to an incoming signed submission.
Every accepted submission is assigned a unique index; that index is bound to that particular
submission for the duration of the election. On election finalization, the next index is
reset to 0.
We can't just use `SignedSubmissionIndices.len()`, because that's a bounded set; past its
capacity, it will simply saturate. We can't just iterate over `SignedSubmissionsMap`,
because iteration is slow. Instead, we store the value here.

items.name: SignedSubmissionIndices
docs: A sorted, bounded set of `(score, index)`, where each `index` points to a value in
`SignedSubmissions`.
We never need to process more than a single signed submission at a time. Signed submissions
can be quite large, so we're willing to pay the cost of multiple database accesses to access
them one at a time instead of reading and decoding all of them at once.

items.name: SignedSubmissionsMap
docs: Unchecked, signed solutions.
Together with `SubmissionIndices`, this stores a bounded set of `SignedSubmissions` while
allowing us to keep only a single one in memory at a time.
Twox note: the key of the map is an auto-incrementing index which users cannot inspect or
affect; we shouldn't need a cryptographically secure hasher.

items.name: MinimumUntrustedScore
docs: The minimum score that each 'untrusted' solution must attain in order to be considered
feasible.
Can be set via `set_minimum_untrusted_score`.

constants.name: UnsignedPhase
docs: Duration of the unsigned phase.

constants.name: SignedPhase
docs: Duration of the signed phase.

constants.name: SolutionImprovementThreshold
docs: The minimum amount of improvement to the solution score that defines a solution as
"better" (in any phase).

constants.name: OffchainRepeat
docs: The repeat threshold of the offchain worker.
For example, if it is 5, that means that at least 5 blocks will elapse between attempts
to submit the worker's solution.

constants.name: MinerTxPriority
docs: The priority of the unsigned transaction submitted in the unsigned-phase

constants.name: MinerMaxIterations
docs: Maximum number of iteration of balancing that will be executed in the embedded miner of
the pallet.

constants.name: MinerMaxWeight
docs: Maximum weight that the miner should consume.
The miner will ensure that the total weight of the unsigned solution will not exceed
this value, based on [`WeightInfo::submit_unsigned`].

constants.name: SignedMaxSubmissions
docs: Maximum number of signed submissions that can be queued.
It is best to avoid adjusting this during an election, as it impacts downstream data
structures. In particular, `SignedSubmissionIndices<T>` is bounded on this value. If you
update this value during an election, you _must_ ensure that
`SignedSubmissionIndices.len()` is less than or equal to the new value. Otherwise,
attempts to submit new solutions may cause a runtime panic.

constants.name: SignedMaxWeight
docs: Maximum weight of a signed solution.
This should probably be similar to [`Config::MinerMaxWeight`].

constants.name: SignedRewardBase
docs: Base reward for a signed solution

constants.name: SignedDepositBase
docs: Base deposit for a signed solution.

constants.name: SignedDepositByte
docs: Per-byte deposit for a signed solution.

constants.name: SignedDepositWeight
docs: Per-weight deposit for a signed solution.

constants.name: MinerMaxLength
docs: Maximum length (bytes) that the mined solution should consume.
The miner will ensure that the total length of the unsigned solution will not exceed
this value.

items.name: HistoryDepth
docs: Number of eras to keep in history.
Information is kept for eras in `[current_era - history_depth; current_era]`.
Must be more than the number of eras delayed by session otherwise. I.e. active era must
always be in history. I.e. `active_era > current_era - history_depth` must be
guaranteed.

items.name: ValidatorCount
docs: The ideal number of staking participants.

items.name: MinimumValidatorCount
docs: Minimum number of staking participants before emergency conditions are imposed.

items.name: Invulnerables
docs: Any validators that may never be slashed or forcibly kicked. It's a Vec since they're
easy to initialize and the performance hit is minimal (we expect no more than four
invulnerables) and restricted to testnets.

items.name: Bonded
docs: Map from all locked "stash" accounts to the controller account.

items.name: MinNominatorBond
docs: The minimum active bond to become and maintain the role of a nominator.

items.name: MinValidatorBond
docs: The minimum active bond to become and maintain the role of a validator.

items.name: Ledger
docs: Map from all (unlocked) "controller" accounts to the info regarding the staking.

items.name: Payee
docs: Where the reward payment should be made. Keyed by stash.

items.name: Validators
docs: The map from (wannabe) validator stash key to the preferences of that validator.
When updating this storage item, you must also update the `CounterForValidators`.

items.name: CounterForValidators
docs: A tracker to keep count of the number of items in the `Validators` map.

items.name: MaxValidatorsCount
docs: The maximum validator count before we stop allowing new validators to join.
When this value is not set, no limits are enforced.

items.name: Nominators
docs: The map from nominator stash key to the set of stash keys of all validators to nominate.
When updating this storage item, you must also update the `CounterForNominators`.

items.name: CounterForNominators
docs: A tracker to keep count of the number of items in the `Nominators` map.

items.name: MaxNominatorsCount
docs: The maximum nominator count before we stop allowing new validators to join.
When this value is not set, no limits are enforced.

items.name: CurrentEra
docs: The current era index.
This is the latest planned era, depending on how the Session pallet queues the validator
set, it might be active or not.

items.name: ActiveEra
docs: The active era information, it holds index and start.
The active era is the era being currently rewarded. Validator set of this era must be
equal to [`SessionInterface::validators`].

items.name: ErasStartSessionIndex
docs: The session index at which the era start for the last `HISTORY_DEPTH` eras.
Note: This tracks the starting session (i.e. session index when era start being active)
for the eras in `[CurrentEra - HISTORY_DEPTH, CurrentEra]`.

items.name: ErasStakers
docs: Exposure of validator at era.
This is keyed first by the era index to allow bulk deletion and then the stash account.
Is it removed after `HISTORY_DEPTH` eras.
If stakers hasn't been set or has been removed then empty exposure is returned.

items.name: ErasStakersClipped
docs: Clipped Exposure of validator at era.
This is similar to [`ErasStakers`] but number of nominators exposed is reduced to the
`T::MaxNominatorRewardedPerValidator` biggest stakers.
(Note: the field `total` and `own` of the exposure remains unchanged).
This is used to limit the i/o cost for the nominator payout.
This is keyed fist by the era index to allow bulk deletion and then the stash account.
Is it removed after `HISTORY_DEPTH` eras.
If stakers hasn't been set or has been removed then empty exposure is returned.

items.name: ErasValidatorPrefs
docs: Similar to `ErasStakers`, this holds the preferences of validators.
This is keyed first by the era index to allow bulk deletion and then the stash account.
Is it removed after `HISTORY_DEPTH` eras.

items.name: ErasValidatorReward
docs: The total validator era payout for the last `HISTORY_DEPTH` eras.
Eras that haven't finished yet or has been removed doesn't have reward.

items.name: ErasRewardPoints
docs: Rewards for the last `HISTORY_DEPTH` eras.
If reward hasn't been set or has been removed then 0 reward is returned.

items.name: ErasTotalStake
docs: The total amount staked for the last `HISTORY_DEPTH` eras.
If total hasn't been set or has been removed then 0 stake is returned.

items.name: ForceEra
docs: Mode of era forcing.

items.name: SlashRewardFraction
docs: The percentage of the slash that is distributed to reporters.
The rest of the slashed value is handled by the `Slash`.

items.name: CanceledSlashPayout
docs: The amount of currency given to reporters of a slash event which was
canceled by extraordinary circumstances (e.g. governance).

items.name: UnappliedSlashes
docs: All unapplied slashes that are queued for later.

items.name: BondedEras
docs: A mapping from still-bonded eras to the first session index of that era.
Must contains information for eras for the range:
`[active_era - bounding_duration; active_era]`

items.name: ValidatorSlashInEra
docs: All slashing events on validators, mapped by era to the highest slash proportion
and slash value of the era.

items.name: NominatorSlashInEra
docs: All slashing events on nominators, mapped by era to the highest slash value of the era.

items.name: SlashingSpans
docs: Slashing spans for stash accounts.

items.name: SpanSlash
docs: Records information about the maximum slash of a stash within a slashing span,
as well as how much reward has been paid out.

items.name: EarliestUnappliedSlash
docs: The earliest era for which we have a pending, unapplied slash.

items.name: CurrentPlannedSession
docs: The last planned session scheduled by the session pallet.
This is basically in sync with the call to [`pallet_session::SessionManager::new_session`].

items.name: StorageVersion
docs: True if network has been upgraded to this version.
Storage version of the pallet.
This is set to v7.0.0 for new networks.

items.name: ChillThreshold
docs: The threshold for when users can start calling `chill_other` for other validators / nominators.
The threshold is compared to the actual number of validators / nominators (`CountFor*`) in
the system compared to the configured max (`Max*Count`).

constants.name: SessionsPerEra
docs: Number of sessions per era.

constants.name: BondingDuration
docs: Number of eras that staked funds must remain bonded for.

constants.name: SlashDeferDuration
docs: Number of eras that slashes are deferred by, after computation.
This should be less than the bonding duration. Set to 0 if slashes
should be applied immediately, without opportunity for intervention.

constants.name: MaxNominatorRewardedPerValidator
docs: The maximum number of nominators rewarded for each validator.
For each validator only the `$MaxNominatorRewardedPerValidator` biggest stakers can claim
their reward. This used to limit the i/o cost for the nominator payout.

items.name: Validators
docs: The current set of validators.

items.name: CurrentIndex
docs: Current index of the session.

items.name: QueuedChanged
docs: True if the underlying economic identities or weighting behind the validators
has changed in the queued validator set.

items.name: QueuedKeys
docs: The queued keys for the next session. When the next session begins, these keys
will be used to determine the validator's session keys.

items.name: DisabledValidators
docs: Indices of disabled validators.
The set is cleared when `on_session_ending` returns a new set of identities.

items.name: NextKeys
docs: The next session keys for a validator.

items.name: KeyOwner
docs: The owner of a key. The key is the `KeyTypeId` + the encoded key.

items.name: PublicPropCount
docs: The number of (public) proposals that have been made so far.

items.name: PublicProps
docs: The public proposals. Unsorted. The second item is the proposal's hash.

items.name: DepositOf
docs: Those who have locked a deposit.
TWOX-NOTE: Safe, as increasing integer keys are safe.

items.name: Preimages
docs: Map of hashes to the proposal preimage, along with who registered it and their deposit.
The block number is the block at which it was deposited.

items.name: ReferendumCount
docs: The next free referendum index, aka the number of referenda started so far.

items.name: LowestUnbaked
docs: The lowest referendum index representing an unbaked referendum. Equal to
`ReferendumCount` if there isn't a unbaked referendum.

items.name: ReferendumInfoOf
docs: Information concerning any given referendum.
TWOX-NOTE: SAFE as indexes are not under an attackers control.

items.name: VotingOf
docs: All votes for a particular voter. We store the balance for the number of votes that we
have recorded. The second item is the total amount of delegations, that will be added.
TWOX-NOTE: SAFE as `AccountId`s are crypto hashes anyway.

items.name: Locks
docs: Accounts for which there are locks in action which may be removed at some point in the
future. The value is the block number at which the lock expires and may be removed.
TWOX-NOTE: OK  `AccountId` is a secure hash.

items.name: LastTabledWasExternal
docs: True if the last referendum tabled was submitted externally. False if it was a public
proposal.

items.name: NextExternal
docs: The referendum to be tabled whenever it would be valid to table an external proposal.
This happens when a referendum needs to be tabled and one of two conditions are met:
- `LastTabledWasExternal` is `false`; or
- `PublicProps` is empty.

items.name: Blacklist
docs: A record of who vetoed what. Maps proposal hash to a possible existent block number
(until when it may not be resubmitted) and who vetoed it.

items.name: Cancellations
docs: Record of all proposals that have been subject to emergency cancellation.

items.name: StorageVersion
docs: Storage version of the pallet.
New networks start with last version.

constants.name: EnactmentPeriod
docs: The minimum period of locking and the period between a proposal being approved and enacted.
It should generally be a little more than the unstake period to ensure that
voting stakers have an opportunity to remove themselves from the system in the case where
they are on the losing side of a vote.

constants.name: LaunchPeriod
docs: How often (in blocks) new public referenda are launched.

constants.name: VotingPeriod
docs: How often (in blocks) to check for new votes.

constants.name: MinimumDeposit
docs: The minimum amount to be used as a deposit for a public referendum proposal.

constants.name: InstantAllowed
docs: Indicator for whether an emergency origin is even allowed to happen. Some chains may want
to set this permanently to `false`, others may want to condition it on things such as
an upgrade having happened recently.

constants.name: FastTrackVotingPeriod
docs: Minimum voting period allowed for a fast-track referendum.

constants.name: CooloffPeriod
docs: Period in blocks where an external proposal may not be re-submitted after being vetoed.

constants.name: PreimageByteDeposit
docs: The amount of balance that must be deposited per byte of preimage stored.

constants.name: MaxVotes
docs: The maximum number of votes for an account.
Also used to compute weight, an overly big value can
lead to extrinsic with very big weight: see `delegate` for instance.

constants.name: MaxProposals
docs: The maximum number of public proposals that can exist at any time.

items.name: Proposals
docs: The hashes of the active proposals.

items.name: ProposalOf
docs: Actual proposal for a given hash, if it's current.

items.name: Voting
docs: Votes on a given proposal, if it is ongoing.

items.name: ProposalCount
docs: Proposals so far.

items.name: Members
docs: The current members of the collective. This is stored sorted (just by value).

items.name: Prime
docs: The prime member that helps determine the default vote behavior in case of absentations.

items.name: Proposals
docs: The hashes of the active proposals.

items.name: ProposalOf
docs: Actual proposal for a given hash, if it's current.

items.name: Voting
docs: Votes on a given proposal, if it is ongoing.

items.name: ProposalCount
docs: Proposals so far.

items.name: Members
docs: The current members of the collective. This is stored sorted (just by value).

items.name: Prime
docs: The prime member that helps determine the default vote behavior in case of absentations.

items.name: Members
docs: The current elected members.
Invariant: Always sorted based on account id.

items.name: RunnersUp
docs: The current reserved runners-up.
Invariant: Always sorted based on rank (worse to best). Upon removal of a member, the
last (i.e. _best_) runner-up will be replaced.

items.name: Candidates
docs: The present candidate list. A current member or runner-up can never enter this vector
and is always implicitly assumed to be a candidate.
Second element is the deposit.
Invariant: Always sorted based on account id.

items.name: ElectionRounds
docs: The total number of vote rounds that have happened, excluding the upcoming one.

items.name: Voting
docs: Votes and locked stake of a particular voter.
TWOX-NOTE: SAFE as `AccountId` is a crypto hash.

constants.name: PalletId
docs: Identifier for the elections-phragmen pallet's lock

constants.name: CandidacyBond
docs: How much should be locked up in order to submit one's candidacy.

constants.name: VotingBondBase
docs: Base deposit associated with voting.
This should be sensibly high to economically ensure the pallet cannot be attacked by
creating a gigantic number of votes.

constants.name: VotingBondFactor
docs: The amount of bond that need to be locked for each vote (32 bytes).

constants.name: DesiredMembers
docs: Number of members to elect.

constants.name: DesiredRunnersUp
docs: Number of runners_up to keep.

constants.name: TermDuration
docs: How long each seat is kept. This defines the next block number at which an election
round will happen. If set to zero, no elections are ever triggered and the module will
be in passive mode.

items.name: Members
docs: The current membership, stored as an ordered Vec.

items.name: Prime
docs: The current prime member, if one exists.

items.name: State
docs: State of the current authority set.

items.name: PendingChange
docs: Pending change: (signaled at, scheduled change).

items.name: NextForced
docs: next block number where we can force a change.

items.name: Stalled
docs: `true` if we are currently stalled.

items.name: CurrentSetId
docs: The number of changes (both in terms of keys and underlying economic responsibilities)
in the "set" of Grandpa validators from genesis.

items.name: SetIdSession
docs: A mapping from grandpa set ID to the index of the *most recent* session for which its
members were responsible.
TWOX-NOTE: `SetId` is not under user control.

items.name: ProposalCount
docs: Number of proposals that have been made.

items.name: Proposals
docs: Proposals that have been made.

items.name: Approvals
docs: Proposal indices that have been approved but not yet awarded.

constants.name: ProposalBond
docs: Fraction of a proposal's value that should be bonded in order to place the proposal.
An accepted proposal gets these back. A rejected proposal does not.

constants.name: ProposalBondMinimum
docs: Minimum amount of funds that should be placed in a deposit for making a proposal.

constants.name: SpendPeriod
docs: Period between successive spends.

constants.name: Burn
docs: Percentage of spare funds (if any) that are burnt per spend period.

constants.name: PalletId
docs: The treasury's pallet id, used for deriving its sovereign account ID.

constants.name: MaxApprovals
docs: The maximum number of approvals that can wait in the spending queue.

items.name: PristineCode
docs: A mapping from an original code hash to the original code, untouched by instrumentation.

items.name: CodeStorage
docs: A mapping between an original code hash and instrumented wasm code, ready for execution.

items.name: AccountCounter
docs: The subtrie counter.

items.name: ContractInfoOf
docs: The code associated with a given account.
TWOX-NOTE: SAFE since `AccountId` is a secure hash.

items.name: DeletionQueue
docs: Evicted contracts that await child trie deletion.
Child trie deletion is a heavy operation depending on the amount of storage items
stored in said trie. Therefore this operation is performed lazily in `on_initialize`.

constants.name: Schedule
docs: Cost schedule and limits.

constants.name: SignedClaimHandicap
docs: Number of block delay an extrinsic claim surcharge has.
When claim surcharge is called by an extrinsic the rent is checked
for current_block - delay

constants.name: TombstoneDeposit
docs: The minimum amount required to generate a tombstone.

constants.name: DepositPerContract
docs: The balance every contract needs to deposit to stay alive indefinitely.
This is different from the [`Self::TombstoneDeposit`] because this only needs to be
deposited while the contract is alive. Costs for additional storage are added to
this base cost.
This is a simple way to ensure that contracts with empty storage eventually get deleted by
making them pay rent. This creates an incentive to remove them early in order to save rent.

constants.name: DepositPerStorageByte
docs: The balance a contract needs to deposit per storage byte to stay alive indefinitely.
Let's suppose the deposit is 1,000 BU (balance units)/byte and the rent is 1 BU/byte/day,
then a contract with 1,000,000 BU that uses 1,000 bytes of storage would pay no rent.
But if the balance reduced to 500,000 BU and the storage stayed the same at 1,000,
then it would pay 500 BU/day.

constants.name: DepositPerStorageItem
docs: The balance a contract needs to deposit per storage item to stay alive indefinitely.
It works the same as [`Self::DepositPerStorageByte`] but for storage items.

constants.name: RentFraction
docs: The fraction of the deposit that should be used as rent per block.
When a contract hasn't enough balance deposited to stay alive indefinitely it needs
to pay per block for the storage it consumes that is not covered by the deposit.
This determines how high this rent payment is per block as a fraction of the deposit.

constants.name: SurchargeReward
docs: Reward that is received by the party whose touch has led
to removal of a contract.

constants.name: DeletionQueueDepth
docs: The maximum number of tries that can be queued for deletion.

constants.name: DeletionWeightLimit
docs: The maximum amount of weight that can be consumed per block for lazy trie removal.

items.name: Key
docs: The `AccountId` of the sudo key.

items.name: HeartbeatAfter
docs: The block number after which it's ok to send heartbeats in the current
session.
At the beginning of each session we set this to a value that should fall
roughly in the middle of the session duration. The idea is to first wait for
the validators to produce a block in the current session, so that the
heartbeat later on will not be necessary.
This value will only be used as a fallback if we fail to get a proper session
progress estimate from `NextSessionRotation`, as those estimates should be
more accurate then the value we calculate for `HeartbeatAfter`.

items.name: Keys
docs: The current set of keys that may issue a heartbeat.

items.name: ReceivedHeartbeats
docs: For each session index, we keep a mapping of `AuthIndex` to
`offchain::OpaqueNetworkState`.

items.name: AuthoredBlocks
docs: For each session index, we keep a mapping of `ValidatorId<T>` to the
number of blocks authored by the given authority.

constants.name: UnsignedPriority
docs: A configuration for base priority of unsigned transactions.
This is exposed so that it can be tuned for particular runtime, when
multiple pallets send unsigned transactions.

items.name: Reports
docs: The primary structure that holds all offence records keyed by report identifiers.

items.name: ConcurrentReportsIndex
docs: A vector of reports of the same kind that happened at the same time slot.

items.name: ReportsByKindIndex
docs: Enumerates all reports of a kind along with the time they happened.
All reports are sorted by the time of offence.
Note that the actual type of this mapping is `Vec<u8>`, this is because values of
different types are not supported at the moment so we are doing the manual serialization.

items.name: RandomMaterial
docs: Series of block headers from the last 81 blocks that acts as random seed material. This
is arranged as a ring buffer with `block_number % 81` being the index into the `Vec` of
the oldest hash.

items.name: IdentityOf
docs: Information that is pertinent to identify the entity behind an account.
TWOX-NOTE: OK  `AccountId` is a secure hash.

items.name: SuperOf
docs: The super-identity of an alternative "sub" identity together with its name, within that
context. If the account is not some other account's sub-identity, then just `None`.

items.name: SubsOf
docs: Alternative "sub" identities of this account.
The first item is the deposit, the second is a vector of the accounts.
TWOX-NOTE: OK  `AccountId` is a secure hash.

items.name: Registrars
docs: The set of registrars. Not expected to get very big as can only be added through a
special origin (likely a council motion).
The index into this can be cast to `RegistrarIndex` to get a valid value.

constants.name: BasicDeposit
docs: The amount held on deposit for a registered identity

constants.name: FieldDeposit
docs: The amount held on deposit per additional field for a registered identity.

constants.name: SubAccountDeposit
docs: The amount held on deposit for a registered subaccount. This should account for the fact
that one storage item's value will increase by the size of an account ID, and there will be
another trie item whose value is the size of an account ID plus 32 bytes.

constants.name: MaxSubAccounts
docs: The maximum number of sub-accounts allowed per identified account.

constants.name: MaxAdditionalFields
docs: Maximum number of additional fields that may be stored in an ID. Needed to bound the I/O
required to access an identity, but can be pretty high.

constants.name: MaxRegistrars
docs: Maxmimum number of registrars allowed in the system. Needed to bound the complexity
of, e.g., updating judgements.

items.name: Founder
docs: The first member.

items.name: Rules
docs: A hash of the rules of this society concerning membership. Can only be set once and
only by the founder.

items.name: Candidates
docs: The current set of candidates; bidders that are attempting to become members.

items.name: SuspendedCandidates
docs: The set of suspended candidates.

items.name: Pot
docs: Amount of our account balance that is specifically for the next round's bid(s).

items.name: Head
docs: The most primary from the most recently approved members.

items.name: Members
docs: The current set of members, ordered.

items.name: SuspendedMembers
docs: The set of suspended members.

items.name: Bids
docs: The current bids, stored ordered by the value of the bid.

items.name: Vouching
docs: Members currently vouching or banned from vouching again

items.name: Payouts
docs: Pending payouts; ordered by block number, with the amount that should be paid out.

items.name: Strikes
docs: The ongoing number of losing votes cast by the member.

items.name: Votes
docs: Double map from Candidate -> Voter -> (Maybe) Vote.

items.name: Defender
docs: The defending member currently being challenged.

items.name: DefenderVotes
docs: Votes for the defender.

items.name: MaxMembers
docs: The max number of members for the society at one time.

constants.name: CandidateDeposit
docs: The minimum amount of a deposit required for a bid to be made.

constants.name: WrongSideDeduction
docs: The amount of the unpaid reward that gets deducted in the case that either a skeptic
doesn't vote or someone votes in the wrong way.

constants.name: MaxStrikes
docs: The number of times a member may vote the wrong way (or not at all, when they are a skeptic)
before they become suspended.

constants.name: PeriodSpend
docs: The amount of incentive paid within each period. Doesn't include VoterTip.

constants.name: RotationPeriod
docs: The number of blocks between candidate/membership rotation periods.

constants.name: ChallengePeriod
docs: The number of blocks between membership challenges.

constants.name: PalletId
docs: The societies's module id

constants.name: MaxCandidateIntake
docs: Maximum candidate intake per round.

items.name: Recoverable
docs: The set of recoverable accounts and their recovery configuration.

items.name: ActiveRecoveries
docs: Active recovery attempts.
First account is the account to be recovered, and the second account
is the user trying to recover the account.

items.name: Proxy
docs: The list of allowed proxy accounts.
Map from the user who can access it to the recovered account.

constants.name: ConfigDepositBase
docs: The base amount of currency needed to reserve for creating a recovery configuration.
This is held for an additional storage item whose value size is
`2 + sizeof(BlockNumber, Balance)` bytes.

constants.name: FriendDepositFactor
docs: The amount of currency needed per additional user when creating a recovery configuration.
This is held for adding `sizeof(AccountId)` bytes more into a pre-existing storage value.

constants.name: MaxFriends
docs: The maximum amount of friends allowed in a recovery configuration.

constants.name: RecoveryDeposit
docs: The base amount of currency needed to reserve for starting a recovery.
This is primarily held for deterring malicious recovery attempts, and should
have a value large enough that a bad actor would choose not to place this
deposit. It also acts to fund additional storage item whose value size is
`sizeof(BlockNumber, Balance + T * AccountId)` bytes. Where T is a configurable
threshold.

items.name: Vesting
docs: Information regarding the vesting of a given account.

constants.name: MinVestedTransfer
docs: The minimum amount transferred to call `vested_transfer`.

items.name: Agenda
docs: Items to be executed, indexed by the block number that they should be executed on.

items.name: Lookup
docs: Lookup from identity to the block number and index of the task.

items.name: StorageVersion
docs: Storage version of the pallet.
New networks start with last version.

constants.name: MaximumWeight
docs: The maximum weight that may be scheduled per block for any dispatchables of less priority
than `schedule::HARD_DEADLINE`.

constants.name: MaxScheduledPerBlock
docs: The maximum number of scheduled calls in the queue for a single block.
Not strictly enforced, but used for weight estimation.

items.name: Proxies
docs: The set of account proxies. Maps the account which has delegated to the accounts
which are being delegated to, together with the amount held on deposit.

items.name: Announcements
docs: The announcements made by the proxy (key).

constants.name: ProxyDepositBase
docs: The base amount of currency needed to reserve for creating a proxy.
This is held for an additional storage item whose value size is
`sizeof(Balance)` bytes and whose key size is `sizeof(AccountId)` bytes.

constants.name: ProxyDepositFactor
docs: The amount of currency needed per proxy added.
This is held for adding 32 bytes plus an instance of `ProxyType` more into a pre-existing
storage value. Thus, when configuring `ProxyDepositFactor` one should take into account
`32 + proxy_type.encode().len()` bytes of data.

constants.name: MaxProxies
docs: The maximum amount of proxies allowed for a single account.

constants.name: MaxPending
docs: The maximum amount of time-delayed announcements that are allowed to be pending.

constants.name: AnnouncementDepositBase
docs: The base amount of currency needed to reserve for creating an announcement.
This is held when a new storage item holding a `Balance` is created (typically 16 bytes).

constants.name: AnnouncementDepositFactor
docs: The amount of currency needed per announcement made.
This is held for adding an `AccountId`, `Hash` and `BlockNumber` (typically 68 bytes)
into a pre-existing storage value.

items.name: Multisigs
docs: The set of open multisig operations.

constants.name: DepositBase
docs: The base amount of currency needed to reserve for creating a multisig execution or to store
a dispatch call for later.
This is held for an additional storage item whose value size is
`4 + sizeof((BlockNumber, Balance, AccountId))` bytes and whose key size is
`32 + sizeof(AccountId)` bytes.

constants.name: DepositFactor
docs: The amount of currency needed per unit threshold when creating a multisig execution.
This is held for adding 32 bytes more into a pre-existing storage value.

constants.name: MaxSignatories
docs: The maximum amount of signatories allowed in the multisig.

items.name: BountyCount
docs: Number of bounty proposals that have been made.

items.name: Bounties
docs: Bounties that have been made.

items.name: BountyDescriptions
docs: The description of each bounty.

items.name: BountyApprovals
docs: Bounty indices that have been approved but not yet funded.

constants.name: DataDepositPerByte
docs: The amount held on deposit per byte within bounty description.

constants.name: BountyDepositBase
docs: The amount held on deposit for placing a bounty proposal.

constants.name: BountyDepositPayoutDelay
docs: The delay period for which a bounty beneficiary need to wait before claim the payout.

constants.name: BountyUpdatePeriod
docs: Bounty duration in blocks.

constants.name: BountyCuratorDeposit
docs: Percentage of the curator fee that will be reserved upfront as deposit for bounty curator.

constants.name: BountyValueMinimum
docs: Minimum value for a bounty.

constants.name: MaximumReasonLength
docs: Maximum acceptable reason length.

items.name: Tips
docs: TipsMap that are not yet completed. Keyed by the hash of `(reason, who)` from the value.
This has the insecure enumerable hash function since the key itself is already
guaranteed to be a secure hash.

items.name: Reasons
docs: Simple preimage lookup from the reason's hash to the original data. Again, has an
insecure enumerable hash since the key is guaranteed to be the result of a secure hash.

constants.name: TipCountdown
docs: The period for which a tip remains open after is has achieved threshold tippers.

constants.name: TipFindersFee
docs: The amount of the final tip which goes to the original reporter of the tip.

constants.name: TipReportDepositBase
docs: The amount held on deposit for placing a tip report.

constants.name: DataDepositPerByte
docs: The amount held on deposit per byte within the tip report reason.

constants.name: MaximumReasonLength
docs: Maximum acceptable reason length.

items.name: Asset
docs: Details of an asset.

items.name: Account
docs: The number of units of assets held by any given account.

items.name: Approvals
docs: Approved balance transfers. First balance is the amount approved for transfer. Second
is the amount of `T::Currency` reserved for storing this.
First key is the asset ID, second key is the owner and third key is the delegate.

items.name: Metadata
docs: Metadata of an asset.

constants.name: AssetDeposit
docs: The basic amount of funds that must be reserved for an asset.

constants.name: MetadataDepositBase
docs: The basic amount of funds that must be reserved when adding metadata to your asset.

constants.name: MetadataDepositPerByte
docs: The additional funds that must be reserved for the number of bytes you store in your
metadata.

constants.name: ApprovalDeposit
docs: The amount of funds that must be reserved when creating a new approval.

constants.name: StringLimit
docs: The maximum length of a name or symbol stored on-chain.

items.name: RootHash
docs: Latest MMR Root hash.

items.name: NumberOfLeaves
docs: Current size of the MMR (number of leaves).

items.name: Nodes
docs: Hashes of the nodes in the MMR.
Note this collection only contains MMR peaks, the inner nodes (and leaves)
are pruned and only stored in the Offchain DB.

items.name: Lottery
docs: The configuration for the current lottery.

items.name: Participants
docs: Users who have purchased a ticket. (Lottery Index, Tickets Purchased)

items.name: TicketsCount
docs: Total number of tickets sold.

items.name: Tickets
docs: Each ticket's owner.
May have residual storage from previous lotteries. Use `TicketsCount` to see which ones
are actually valid ticket mappings.

items.name: CallIndices
docs: The calls stored in this pallet to be used in an active lottery if configured
by `Config::ValidateCall`.

constants.name: PalletId
docs: The Lottery's pallet id

constants.name: MaxCalls
docs: The max number of calls available in a single lottery.

constants.name: MaxGenerateRandom
docs: Number of time we should try to generate a random number that has no modulo bias.
The larger this number, the more potential computation is used for picking the winner,
but also the more likely that the chosen winner is done fairly.

items.name: QueueTotals
docs: The totals of items and balances within each queue. Saves a lot of storage reads in the
case of sparsely packed queues.
The vector is indexed by duration in `Period`s, offset by one, so information on the queue
whose duration is one `Period` would be storage `0`.

items.name: Queues
docs: The queues of bids ready to become gilts. Indexed by duration (in `Period`s).

items.name: ActiveTotal
docs: Information relating to the gilts currently active.

items.name: Active
docs: The currently active gilts, indexed according to the order of creation.

constants.name: IgnoredIssuance
docs: The issuance to ignore. This is subtracted from the `Currency`'s `total_issuance` to get
the issuance by which we inflate or deflate the gilt.

constants.name: QueueCount
docs: Number of duration queues in total. This sets the maximum duration supported, which is
this value multiplied by `Period`.

constants.name: MaxQueueLen
docs: Maximum number of items that may be in each duration queue.

constants.name: FifoQueueLen
docs: Portion of the queue which is free from ordering and just a FIFO.
Must be no greater than `MaxQueueLen`.

constants.name: Period
docs: The base period for the duration queues. This is the common multiple across all
supported freezing durations that can be bid upon.

constants.name: MinFreeze
docs: The minimum amount of funds that may be offered to freeze for a gilt. Note that this
does not actually limit the amount which may be frozen in a gilt since gilts may be
split up in order to satisfy the desired amount of funds under gilts.
It should be at least big enough to ensure that there is no possible storage spam attack
or queue-filling attack.

constants.name: IntakePeriod
docs: The number of blocks between consecutive attempts to issue more gilts in an effort to
get to the target amount to be frozen.
A larger value results in fewer storage hits each block, but a slower period to get to
the target.

constants.name: MaxIntakeBids
docs: The maximum amount of bids that can be turned into issued gilts each block. A larger
value here means less of the block available for transactions should there be a glut of
bids to make into gilts to reach the target.

items.name: Class
docs: Details of an asset class.

items.name: Account
docs: The assets held by any given account; set out this way so that assets owned by a single
account can be enumerated.

items.name: Asset
docs: The assets in existence and their ownership details.

items.name: ClassMetadataOf
docs: Metadata of an asset class.

items.name: InstanceMetadataOf
docs: Metadata of an asset instance.

items.name: Attribute
docs: Metadata of an asset class.

constants.name: ClassDeposit
docs: The basic amount of funds that must be reserved for an asset class.

constants.name: InstanceDeposit
docs: The basic amount of funds that must be reserved for an asset instance.

constants.name: MetadataDepositBase
docs: The basic amount of funds that must be reserved when adding metadata to your asset.

constants.name: AttributeDepositBase
docs: The basic amount of funds that must be reserved when adding an attribute to an asset.

constants.name: DepositPerByte
docs: The additional funds that must be reserved for the number of bytes store in metadata,
either "normal" metadata or attribute metadata.

constants.name: StringLimit
docs: The maximum length of data stored on-chain.

constants.name: KeyLimit
docs: The maximum length of an attribute key.

constants.name: ValueLimit
docs: The maximum length of an attribute value.

items.name: Transactions
docs: Collection of transaction metadata by block number.

items.name: ChunkCount
docs: Count indexed chunks for each block.

items.name: ByteFee
docs: Storage fee per byte.

items.name: EntryFee
docs: Storage fee per transaction.

items.name: MaxTransactionSize
docs: Maximum data set in a single transaction in bytes.

items.name: MaxBlockTransactions
docs: Maximum number of indexed transactions in the block.

items.name: StoragePeriod
docs: Storage period for data in blocks. Should match `sp_storage_proof::DEFAULT_STORAGE_PERIOD`
for block authoring.

items.name: ProofChecked
docs: Was the proof checked in this block?
